cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about object detection using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed Bidirectional Pyramid Networks (BPN) framework involves novel components for feature representation and anchor refinement, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments and evaluations on datasets, which could be related to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
